                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>A <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000I.xml" title="functor between precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000I" type="local">functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F\colon  C \to  D]]></fr:tex> is called (<html:em><html:strong>full</html:strong></html:em>, <html:em><html:strong>faithful</html:strong></html:em>) when the action on arrows is valued in (<fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0029.xml" title="surjection" addr="forest://erct/erct-0029" type="local">surjections</fr:link>, <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003K.xml" title="embedding" addr="forest://erct/erct-003K" type="local">embeddings</fr:link>) respectively. It is common to refer to a <html:em>full</html:em> and <html:em>faithful</html:em> functor as <html:em><html:strong>fully faithful</html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
                    <html:p>Fullness and faithfulness are both <html:em><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">properties</fr:link></html:em> of a functor.</html:p>
