                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>A <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000I.xml" title="functor between precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000I" type="local">functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F\colon  C \to  D]]></fr:tex> is called an <html:em><html:strong>isomorphism</html:strong></html:em>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  C\cong  D]]></fr:tex>, when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000K.xml" title="full and faithful functor" addr="forest://erct/erct-000K" type="local">fully faithful</fr:link> and its action on objects is an equivalence of types.</html:p>
                    <html:p>Being an isomorphism is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</html:p>
