}}{D\cong  C}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000J.xml" title="isomorphism of precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000J" type="local">isomorphisms of precategories</fr:link> onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-000L/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000L/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="the univalence principle for precategories › forest://erct/erct-000L/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000L.xml" title="the univalence principle for precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000L" type="local">the univalence principle for <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link></fr:link> › forest://erct/erct-000L/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>The type of isomorphisms onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is inhabited, considering the identity isomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{C}\colon  C\cong  C]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, it suffices to show that the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000J.xml" title="isomorphism of precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000J" type="local">isomorphisms</fr:link> onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> depicted below is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   \begin {aligned}
    D &: \mathsf {Precategory}\\
    F &: D\cong  C
   \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>We unfold the definitions of a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000J.xml" title="isomorphism of precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000J" type="local">their isomorphisms</fr:link>, dropping <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">propositional</fr:link> axioms:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\
      D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_0&: D_0\to  C_0\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\to  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_0x,F_0y\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\\
      h_1 &: \mathsf {isBiinvertible}\,F_0\\
      h_2 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} \mathsf {isPropMap}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_1xy\right \rparen \mathclose {}

      \\
      h_3 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
