    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>A function that is both <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0029.xml" title="surjection" addr="forest://erct/erct-0029" type="local">surjection</fr:link>, i.e. a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003F.xml" title="bijection" addr="forest://erct/erct-003F" type="local">bijection</fr:link>, is an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000V.xml" title="equivalence of types" addr="forest://erct/erct-000V" type="local">equivalence</fr:link> by <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002Z.xml" title="bijections are biinvertible" addr="forest://erct/erct-002Z" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002Z" /></fr:link>. We can therefore repackage our telescope equivalently:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\
      D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_0&: D_0\cong  C_0\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\cong  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_0x,F_0y\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>By the univalence principle for types, we may contract 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen D_0,F_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
 to 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen 
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
, 1_{
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
}\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_1&:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\cong  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>Next we rewrite using the univalence principles for functions and families of types (<fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0015.xml" title="the univalence principle for dependent functions" addr="forest://erct/erct-0015" type="local">Axiom <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-0015" /></fr:link>, <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001D.xml" title="the univalence principle for types" addr="forest://erct/erct-001D" type="local">Axiom <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001D" /></fr:link>):</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_1&:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_1&: D_1 = \lambda {x,y}\mathpunct {.}{C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>By the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0015.xml" title="the univalence principle for dependent functions" addr="forest://erct/erct-0015" type="local">univalence principle for functions</fr:link>, the data above is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>31</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-0030</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0030.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="natural transformation">natural transformation</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0030.agda" type="external">erct-0030.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F,G\colon  C\to  D]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000I.xml" title="functor between precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000I" type="local">functors</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>. A <html:em><html:strong>natural transformation</html:strong></html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \colon  F\to  G]]></fr:tex> is given by a family of arrows <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _\bullet \colon \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}D
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen Fx,Gx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> equipped with a (necessarily unique) naturality datum <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _f\colon  \alpha _y\circ  Ff = Gf\circ  \alpha _x]]></fr:tex> for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  x\to  y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-000F</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000F.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="section-retraction pair in a precategory">section-retraction pair in a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>section-retraction pair</html:strong></html:em> in a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> consists of an arrow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  x \to  y]]></fr:tex> called the <html:em>section</html:em> and an arrow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\colon  y \to  x]]></fr:tex> called the <html:em>retraction</html:em> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\circ  s = 1_{x}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-000G</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000G.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="isomorphism in a precategory">isomorphism in a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000G.agda" type="external">erct-000G.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>An arrow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  x \to  y]]></fr:tex> in a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is called an <html:em><html:strong>isomorphism</html:strong></html:em> when either of there exists an inverse to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>, i.e. an arrow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  y \to  x]]></fr:tex> that is simultaneously a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000F.xml" title="section-retraction pair in a precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000F" type="local">section and a retraction</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
                <html:p>We shall write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  x \cong  y]]></fr:tex> to denote an isomorphism from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-000D</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000D.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="univalent precategory">univalent <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000D.agda" type="external">erct-000D.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is called <html:em><html:strong>univalent</html:strong></html:em> when for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  C]]></fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}y\cong  x]]></fr:tex> of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000G.xml" title="isomorphism in a precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000G" type="local">isomorphisms</fr:link> onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-000H</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000H.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="category">category</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000H.agda" type="external">erct-000H.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>category</html:strong></html:em> is defined to be a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000D.xml" title="univalent precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000D" type="local">univalent</fr:link> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>The material on univalent category theory is drawn primarily from the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/hottbook.xml" title="Homotopy Type Theory: univalent foundations of mathematics" addr="forest://erct/hottbook" type="local">HoTT Book</fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/ahrens-kapulkin-shulman-2015.xml" title="Univalent categories and the Rezk completion" addr="forest://erct/ahrens-kapulkin-shulman-2015" type="local">Ahrens, Kapulkin, and Shulman</fr:link>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
